## Project Description
This project implements a machine learning model to classify Iris flower species using sepal and petal measurements. A K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) classifier is trained and evaluated to demonstrate basic classification concepts.

## Dataset
- Iris Dataset
- Features: Sepal Length, Sepal Width, Petal Length, Petal Width
- Target: Species (Setosa, Versicolor, Virginica)

## Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas, NumPy
- Scikit-learn
- Matplotlib

## Workflow
1. Load and preprocess the dataset
2. Encode target labels
3. Split data into training and testing sets
4. Train KNN classifier
5. Evaluate model accuracy
6. Predict species for new samples

## Results
The model achieves high accuracy and correctly predicts Iris flower species.

## How to Run
1. Place `Iris.csv` in the project folder
2. Run the Python script or notebook
3. View predictions and visualizations

